<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="supp-description" xml:lang="en">
    <head>Physical description</head>

    <div rend="tag-defs">
        <head>Relevant element documentation:</head>
        <p>
            <specList>
                <specDesc key="physDesc"/>
            </specList>
        </p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <p>Information describing the physical aspects of an inscription is encoded in the
                <gi>physDesc</gi> element, which is part of the <gi>teiHeader</gi>.</p>

        <p>The following subsections of these guidelines address specific aspects of this
            encoding:</p>
        <list style="clear:both">
            <item>
                <ref target="supp-descobject.html">Description and dimensions of monument or
                    object</ref>
            </item>
            <item>
                <ref target="supp-desctext.html">Description and layout of text field or
                    campus</ref>
            </item>
            <item>
                <ref target="supp-descletters.html">Description of letters or hands</ref>
            </item>
            <item>
                <ref target="supp-descdecor.html">Decoration or iconography</ref>
            </item>
            <item>
                <ref target="supp-descdimensions.html">Dimensions (of object, campus or
                    letters)</ref>
            </item>
        </list>

        <p>If, rather than breaking down the description of various aspects of the support, the
            editor prefers a single unstructured prose passage describing the object, the
                <gi>physDesc</gi> may contain one or more <gi>p</gi> (paragraph) elements as an
            alternative to (but not in addition to) the structured elements described in the
            sections linked above.</p>

        <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
            <physDesc>
                <objectDesc>
                    <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                            <p><material>Bronze</material> Sextarius</p>
                        </support>
                    </supportDesc>
                    <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>inscribed on the outside just below the rim</layout>
                    </layoutDesc>
                </objectDesc>
                <handDesc>
                    <handNote>Fourth-century A.D. script; <height>0.02</height>
                    </handNote>
                </handDesc>
            </physDesc>
        </egXML>

        <p>You can align your definitions by aligning to a local or to an external <ref target="idx-nontei.html">Controlled Vocabulary</ref>.</p>
        
    </div>

